## Tech stack
- Web: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Radix UI
- Mobile: Expo SDK 51, React Native, Expo Router
- Database: Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Edge Functions + Realtime)
- CMS: Sanity.io (content editable by church staff without developer)
- Hosting: Vercel (web) + EAS Build (mobile)
- CDN + DNS + Storage: Cloudflare (R2 for media)
- Email: Resend + React Email
- Push notifications: OneSignal
- Giving: Zeffy (embed) + PayPal Giving Fund (future, when 501c3)
- PDF generation: @react-pdf/renderer (server-side, free)
- Transcription: OpenAI Whisper API
- Translation: DeepL API (Phase 3)
- i18n: next-intl (/es /fr /pt /zh routes)
- Package manager: pnpm

## Auth roles (Supabase RLS enforced at Postgres level)
- public: anonymous, no login — can read published content, submit public prayers, RSVP
- member: magic link login — own giving history, private prayers, member resources
- staff: church team — all prayers, events admin, sermon upload, financial dashboard
- admin: Director of Technology (you) — full access, role management, Supabase Studio

## Database tables (14 total)
profiles, sermons, sermon_series, prayer_requests, events, rsvps,
blog_posts, email_subscribers, members, small_groups, giving_records,
expenses, notification_prefs, translations

## Key architectural rules
1. Business logic lives in packages/db and packages/cms — never duplicated in apps
2. Both apps import from packages/* — never from each other
3. Server Components (RSC) for all data fetching in Next.js — no useEffect for data
4. Supabase client in packages/db/client.ts — one instance, used by both apps
5. All Sanity GROQ queries in packages/cms/queries/ — never inline in components
6. RLS enforced in Postgres — middleware is a second layer, not the only layer
7. All media files go to Cloudflare R2 — never Supabase Storage
8. PDF generation runs server-side via Next.js API routes — never client-side
9. Environment variables: NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix for client-safe vars only

## Next.js app route groups
- (public)/ — Home, Sermons, Events, Give, Prayer, Blog, About, Beliefs, Visit, Contact, Resources, Live
- (member)/ — Dashboard, Groups, Resources (auth-gated: role=member)
- (staff)/ — Prayer, Sermons, Events, Blog, Financials, Members (auth-gated: role=staff)
- [locale]/ — /es /fr /pt /zh multilingual routes
- studio/ — Sanity Studio embedded
- api/ — tithing-statement, financial-report, webhooks, revalidate

## Mobile app tabs (Expo Router)
- (tabs)/home — Service times, Watch Live, events strip, latest sermon
- (tabs)/sermons — Archive, search, player, offline download
- (tabs)/give — Zeffy webview, giving history (member)
- (tabs)/prayer — Submit request, own requests (member), triage (staff)
- (tabs)/more — Events, Blog, Resources, Notifications, Account

## Giving system
- Primary: Zeffy iframe embed on /give page — 0% fees, church keeps 100%
- Zeffy API (read-only) syncs giving data to Supabase giving_records table nightly
- Future: PayPal Giving Fund button activates via Sanity CMS config toggle (no code change)

## Financial features
- Individual tithing statements: PDF generated via @react-pdf/renderer
  - Member downloads own from portal anytime
  - Staff generates for any member on demand
  - Pastor triggers bulk email to all members at year end
  - API route: GET /api/tithing-statement?year=YYYY&memberId=xxx
- Church financial dashboard: /staff/financials (staff + admin only)
  - Income: auto-populated from Zeffy sync (giving_records table)
  - Expenses: manually entered by pastor or treasurer via simple form
  - Annual report PDF: GET /api/financial-report?year=YYYY
  - PDF stored in Cloudflare R2 bucket: lsc-financials

## Cloudflare R2 buckets
- lsc-media: sermon audio, thumbnails, staff photos, event images
- lsc-docs: PDFs, books, study materials
- lsc-captions: .vtt and .srt caption files per sermon
- lsc-financials: tithing statement PDFs, annual report PDFs, expense receipts
- Custom domain: media.lschurch.com

## AI pipeline (Whisper transcription)
1. Pastor uploads video → Cloudflare R2
2. Supabase Edge Function (whisper-transcribe) triggers on sermon INSERT
3. Fetches audio from R2 → sends to OpenAI Whisper API
4. Stores timestamped JSON transcript in sermons.transcript
5. Generates .vtt captions → uploads to lsc-captions R2 bucket
6. Calls Vercel ISR revalidation → sermon page rebuilds with transcript
7. Phase 3: deepl-translate Edge Function sends to DeepL for multilingual subtitles

## SEO requirements
- generateMetadata() on every route — unique titles and descriptions
- Schema.org/Church in root layout
- Schema.org/VideoObject on every sermon page
- Schema.org/Event on every event page
- Schema.org/FAQPage on Home and Plan a Visit
- next-sitemap auto-generates XML sitemap on every build
- @vercel/og generates Open Graph images per sermon/event/blog post
- hreflang tags on all multilingual routes (Phase 3)

## Design system
- Tailwind CSS with custom design tokens
- Primary: #1B4F8A (blue), #0F7B6C (teal), #B45309 (amber)
- Body font: Inter (web), System font stack (mobile)
- Radix UI for all interactive components (dialogs, menus, dropdowns)
- 44x44px minimum tap targets on all interactive elements

## Prompt pattern for agents
Always specify:
1. Exact file path (e.g. apps/web/app/(staff)/financials/page.tsx)
2. Whether it's RSC or client component
3. Which existing query/utility to use from packages/
4. Which UI component to import from packages/ui/
5. Any metadata or schema requirements

